<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 26  9:39:03 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I first visited The Wall with two friends from Vietnam; I have visited it alone twice since then.  Each visit has resulted in ambivalent feelings.  In some ways, the first visit was anti-climatic.  I had heard about The Wall for years and had even visited a &quot;traveling Wall&quot; exhibition.  I am not sure what I expected from my first visit--release, perhaps.  One clear emotion was anger at the fatigue-clad vendors, preying on the visitors and perpetuating the MIA myth.  Overall, when I stand before the wall, I have a feeling not of why but of how.  How could we have allowed that war to drag on so long?  My most moving experience in relation to The Wall was a visit last spring to the exhibition at the Smithsonian of items left at The Wall by family and friends of the people represented on The Wall.   ---a former grunt
